The '''Print Room''' at [[Windsor Castle]] is a [[print room]] which is an office in the [[Royal Collection]] Department of the [[Royal Household]] of the [[Monarch|Sovereign]] of the [[United Kingdom]]. It is responsible for the care and maintenance of the royal collections of [[drawing]]s and [[old master print]]s ([[engraving]]s etc.), which is one of the finest in the world.{{Citation needed|date=September 2011}} The term refers to both an institution and a room, and is under the direction of the Head of Prints and Drawings, currently [[Martin Clayton]] [[RVO|MVO]].<ref>[http://royaldrawingschool.org/about/people/external-assessment-board-old/martin-clayton-mvo-fsa/ Martin Clayton MVO FSA.] [[Royal Drawing School]]. Retrieved 20 April 2016.</ref>

